# LoCoD

## Tips for petalinux build for ultra96 board
First, export Hardware from Vivado.

Second, create petalinux project

    petalinux-create -t project -n ultra96-locod --template zynqMP

Third, get hardware description in petalinux project

    petalinux-config --get-hw-description ../project_path/

Forth, configure petalinux project for ultra96 board

    petalinux-config ---> DTG Settings ---> (zcu100-revc) MACHINE_NAME
    petalinux-config ---> u-boot Configuration ---> (xilinx_zynqmp_zcu100_revC_defconfig) u-boot config target
    petalinux-config ---> Yocto Settings ---> (ultra96-zynqmp) YOCTO_MACHINE_NAME

Build project

    petalinux-build

Build boot imgages

    petalinux-package --boot --format BIN --fsbl images/linux/zynqmp_fsbl.elf --u-boot images/linux/u-boot.elf --pmufw images/linux/pmufw.elf --fpga images/linux/system.bit



